<div class="quotetitle">drk421 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Scrolling sounds like the most difficult part.<br /></div><br />Scrolling by itself isn't difficult at all: just tell the NES what part of the name tables you want visible and it just happens. Synchronizing name table updates to the position of the scroll is the hard part.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I remember C64 sprites were very easy to use.<br /></div><br />NES sprites are easy too. The only issue is that they are quite small, so you need a good number of them grouped together in order to display something meaningful.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Jul 02, 2009 9:37 am</p><hr />
